Press Release<br /><!-- NewsDate.start -->
			February 6, 2006<!-- NewsDate.end --><p style="text-align: center"><span class="PRTitle"><!-- NewsTitle.start -->APPOINTMENT OF NEW 
			DENR SECRETARY AN <br />OFFSHOOT OF HAPHAZARD PALACE DECISION
			</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">
			Senate Minority Leader Aquilino Nene Q. Pimentel, Jr. (PDP-Laban) 
			today voiced apprehension that the government may fall short of its 
			responsibility to protest and preserve the countrys forest, marine 
			and other natural resources and to maintain ecological balance in 
			view of President Gloria Macapagal-Arroyos decision to appoint a 
			secretary of environment and natural resources without any 
			background, and much less interest, in this area of government 
			concern.<br /><br />Pimentel said Secretary Angelo Reyes, newly-appointed head of the 
			Department of Environment and Natural Resources, may be the wrong 
			man for the job, leaving the enormous task of preventing 
			environmental degradation uncertain.<br /><br />He said it is an open secret that Reyes preferred to stay as 
			secretary of interior and local government because he is more at 
			home there and did not like to be transferred to the DENR where he 
			felt he may be ineffective because is a strange field to him.<br /><br />President Gloria Macapagal-Arroyo owes the public an explanation 
			why she placed Reyes, a military man, as DENR secretary when ideally 
			and by tradition, this position should be held by a person who is an 
			environmentalist by training and inclination, Pimentel said.<br /><br />The minority leader said every indication points to the fact that 
			Reyes reassignment to the DENR is a product of accommodation in view 
			of Malaca&ntilde;ang
s decision to replace him with Antipolo Rep. Ronaldo 
			Puno at the DILG.<br /><br />Pimentel said the Palace wants Puno to take over the helm of the 
			DILG so that the administration can make use of his expertise as a 
			political operator par excellence in mobilizing the local 
			government chief executives for the forthcoming launching of 
			peoples initiative for Charter Change, the main aim of which is to 
			perpetuate President Arroyo in power despite doubts over her 
			legitimacy.<br /><br />He said the appointment of Reyes is not a product of a carefully 
			thought-of idea to maximize the benefits from utilization of natural 
			resources or strictly implement environmental safeguards especially 
			in the face of expanded mining operations by foreign mining 
			companies.<br /><br />On the contrary, Pimentel said Reyes was transferred to the DENR as 
			a fallback position after he rejected the Palaces plan to appoint 
			him ambassador to Washington D.C.</p><!-- NewsBody.end --></td>
